<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-07-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-07-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="847" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d847">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/12637.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Brazilian Minister</gloss> to Mexico.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-07-28">
                                    <hi rend="italic">July 28, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>181 bis. Suitable instructions are today being telegraphed to Vice Consul
                            Silliman at Tampico for presentation to Carranza in accordance with your
                            100, July 27. Names of Constitutionalist delegates will be telegraphed
                            as soon as received.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">W. J. Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>